          <title>No. 2 Oregon routs Purdue 35-0, remains on top of Big Ten with first road shutout in over 30 years</title>
          <description><![CDATA[WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. (AP) — Oregon coach Dan Lanning challenged his team to see how it would respond to a long road trip on a short week following its 32-31 victory over then-No. 2 Ohio State last week. The No. 2 Ducks aced that test Friday night.]]></description>
